            "message": "Site variables can be used to create reusable text content across all pages of your site. The benefit of using a site variable is that if you change the value here, it will automatically change everywhere it's used.\r\n\r\nFor example, you might create site variable for your office hours:\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Add a variable below with the name <em>office-hours<\/em> and the value <em>Monday-Friday, 9AM - 5PM<\/em><\/li>\r\n<li>Anywhere you want the value to show, add this shortcode: <em>[site-variable office-hours]<\/em><\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n\r\nNow, if your office hours change, you can update it here and it will be reflected everywhere you used the shortcode.",
